Northeast Kentucky Fish and Game Association

Address: Herbert Ross Dr., Cannonsburg, Kentucky

Website: http://nekfga.com/

When: August 11-12, 2012
Check-in starts at 8:30 AM. Course of Instruction begins at 9:00 AM each day.

Range Fee: All attendees (except NEKF&G members) - $5.00 Per person per event  This extra fee is collected on the day of the shoot and goes to the host range for use of their facility.

Camping available: No camping on grounds.  No known campgrounds within ½ hr. of range.

Hotels:  Holiday Inn 15 minutes away, Hampton Inn 15 minutes away, Fairfield Inn 20 minutes away.

Ross Drive and turn left (there will be a sign and a gate at the entrance).  Once on Herbert C. Ross, at the top of the hill turn right onto Long Shot.  The range will be on the right.

GPS: N38.35563 W82.72844

State Laws to be aware of: Check State Laws http://www.nraila.org/statelawpdfs/KYSL.pdf

Misc:  This is a .22lr rimfire ONLY event. Shoot your rimfire rifle at 25 meters.  

The range being used may not be sheltered.  If it's sunny, you may be out in the sun.  If raining, you may be out in the rain.  Bring what's appropriate for you and bring cover for your rifle if rain is expected. Events are not canceled due to the weather (with the exception of extreme weather, i.e. - tornado, severe storms/lightning). 

There will be a designated time for lunch and history. There is no food or water available on site.  Participants are encouraged to stay on site through lunch. Please bring what food you need or be prepared to have your order delivered to the range. I thought parting with this would be a good way for it to find some love…and maybe get me an optic or other stuff for my AR. ?

It’s a BUL Cherokee Compact in 9mm.(A polymer framed version of the CZ75 made in Israel.)  It hasn’t been shot very much at all.  I ran three mixed magazines of different types of ammo and it ran like a champ, then it went into the safe.  It has a 17-round factory mag and two 16-round ProMags, all of which function perfectly.  The original box with the manual, test-fire case, and a mini-cleaning kit(unused) are included.  I found a Blackhawk leather OWB holster that fits it like a glove and it will come with that, as well.

The brass tacks…I love to trade, but for a cash price I’d like to get $425 OBO for the whole carry package.  I’d like to try and keep it close to Central Ohio for a FTF transaction.  As far as trade interests go, well the list is long but I’ll hit the high points and I’m pretty sure you’ll get the idea. ?

Optics suitable for an AR.(BIG dreams first: Eotech or Aimpoint)
I can add some cash for the right deal, but limited funds is why I prefer to trade.
I liked the look of the Burris AR-536, too.

AR Mags, more mags, and more mags. I really like the Pmags and didn’t dislike the C-Products nor the Thermold’s.  Wouldn’t mind trying the Lancers, though.

5.56 Ammo…what good is an AR without ammo for the lots of mags? ?

Sling, I really like what I’ve read and seen on the Savvy Sniper Quad sling, so something along those lines.

Mix and match, as long as we both are happy with the deal, the options are endless.
